summary:
I. Love. This. Scene.
One of the best of the entire series.
Telling a blind man that you were told he wanted to see you while...
body:
I. Love. This. Scene.

One of the best of the entire series.

  • Telling a blind man that you were told he wanted to see you while the blind man is wielding a fucking meat cleaver like it’s nothing
  • Finding the only grown man in Castle Black who is shorter than you
  • Look of utter disgust at raw meat while your aunt is eating a whole fucking horse heart
  • Mope and brood and mope and brood
  • Act like you don’t wonder why the rules are what they are, you don’t make them, you just follow them
  • Act like a 100 year old man doesn’t know anything
  • Believe you’re the only person to feel what you feel, and you feel it more than anyone has ever felt anything before
  • Get laughed at by an old man when you try to say he doesn’t understand
  • Feel yourself shrinking when old man tells you that 1) he’s fucking royalty, bitch and 2) his whole family was butchered
  • “And his poor son”
  • (That’s your dad, yo)
  • “And the children! Even the little children
  • (Those were your siblings BTW, your brother and sister)
  • Realize that the world, in fact, does not revolve around you and your emo life
  • Realize you’re speaking to a legend
  • Ultimately still don’t listen, go off, be an idiot
  • Come to respect the man after whom you will name your son one day, realize 7 years later that he was right about everything when you might have to choose between duty and love

summary: That's why I roll my eyes when I see the argument that Sansa won't be very prominent because Sophie finished her scenes early....
question: That's why I roll my eyes when I see the argument that Sansa won't be very prominent because Sophie finished her scenes early. Do they know anything about filming? Obviously, Sophie's scenes will be easier and quicker to film than that of Kit, Maisie or Emilia's, because they will likely be in the thick of battle and battle scenes usually need constant reshoots, while Sophie won't be doing all that, so of course she will likely finish earlier than others.
answer: Plus her scenes won’t use CGI or a large number of extras. It’s just wishful thinking at this point. They want her dead or irrelevant so they hold on to the only evidence they have

summary: Lady Crane died too soon. D&D had the chance to merge her character with Lady Smallwood's and introduce her a bit earlier in...
body:
Lady Crane died too soon. D&D had the chance to merge her character with Lady Smallwood’s and introduce her a bit earlier in season 5 for Arya’s storyline. Although I guess more screen time couldnt be sacrificed and that “Bad Pussy” scene was essential.

It’s a pity to see the under-used talent of Essie Davis and the lack in further development of Arya’s and Lady Crane’s relationship. Just think about it though.

Arya sees Lady Crane as a mother figure and is reminded of her family back in Westeros. Arya’s choice to become a cold, unfeeling assassin or Arya Stark of Winterfell becomes much harder. This conflict becomes more prevalent in Arya.

I guess we have to settle on 2 little conversations between Arya and Crane, and the questionable stabbing scene where Arya has super healing and there’s no real consequences. Lady Crane’s role and death could have been more impactful on Arya if she was set up and developed earlier. Arya seeing the ugly side of the Faceless Men and Arya rejecting the Faceless Men could have been a more powerful scene.

For now, we’ll have to deal with Arya being the distant, cold executioner of House Stark (despite Arya rejecting that path when she walked out of the House of Black and White) alongside her brother, cold and distant interface, Bran Version 2.003.01 of House Stark.

However, Maisie mentioning that the next season will be more light-hearted for Arya and she’ll have different goals is giving me hope.
